<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06242224 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06242224 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  POLICE; PROBE; M; PAST; MURDER; LOS-GATOS; MAN  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  In an effort to shed new light on the investigation of a 1989 homicide, LosGatos police have set up a toll-free line for the public and have called in anagent from the state Department of Justice's Bureau of Investigation.;   Anearlier trial of two women for the Oct. 3, 1989 beating death of Vincent Ferlaat his Thurston Avenue home ended in a mistrial.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  LOS GATOS POLICE BROADEN MURDER CASE INVESTIGATION  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Officials believed the investigation was nearing completion late last yearwith the arrests of Patricia &quot;Patsy&quot; Robertson, 43, and Lisa Duren, 28, bothof San Jose.;   In a statement to police, which she later recanted, Robertsonadmitted killing Ferla, 59.;   But as attorneys for the pair were makingclosing arguments in Santa Clara County Superior Court in February, a newwitness came forward implicating another person. Judge John Schatz dismissedjurors and declared a mistrial.; IF YOU'RE INTERESTED; Anyone with informationabout the case is asked to call the Los Gatos Police Department hot line at(800) 283-3752.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  ROBERT S. KLINDT, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910829  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  166  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, August 29, 199100242224,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>